en_790136_0	‘Angampora,’ Sri Lankan Martial Art, Basic Course No 2 at the Security Force Headquarters - Kilinochchi (SFHQ-KLN) in order to introduce and popularize this ancient self-defence techniques, promotion of physical strength, endurance, courage and tolerance among the soldiers, commenced under the guidance of Major General Vijitha Ravipriya, Commander, Security Forces - Kilinochchi for Army personnel serving in Kilinochchi areas.
en_790136_1	The inaugural ceremony of the course was held on Thursday (3) at the Dasa Bala Rawana Experiment and Conservation Angampora Village.
en_790136_2	Commander, Security Forces - Kilinochchi, graced the opening ceremony as the Chief Guest along with Staff Officers in the SFHQ-KLN.
en_790136_3	Angampora Instructor, Ritigala Sinhakkara Parapure Kalakeerthi Kalavibushana, Mr Devinda Laksiri Ranasinghe will be the in charge for the entire period of the course and 32 male Army personnel from under command Battalions in Kilinochchi are participating in the course.
